ronymic from the personal name <i>Erland</i>, from the Old Norse byname <i>Erlandr</i>, meaning ‘foreign, from a foreign country’.","Americanized form of Norwegian and Danish   Erlandsen  , a cognate of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Erlandsen","meanings":["Norwegian and Danish: patronymic from the personal name <i>Erland</i> (see   Erlandson  )."]},{"name":"Erland","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Obert.","Norwegian: habitational name from a farm in southwestern Norway so named, from Old Norse <i>elri</i> ‘alder’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’, ‘farm’.","Probably also an American shortened form of Swedish <b>Erlandsson</b> (see   Erlandson  )."]}]},{"name":"Kagg","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of Swiss German and South German <b>Kägi</b>: topographic name from <i>Gehegi</i>, from Middle High German <i>gehage</i> ‘hedge, fence’ (see   Kage  ).","In some cases possibly also South German (<b>Kägy</b>): variant of <b>Kägi</b> (see 1 above). This surname is very rare in Germany."],"variants":[{"name":"Kage","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Claus, Hermann, Wilhelm.","German:","topographic name from a shortened form of Middle High German <i>gehage</i> ‘hedge, fence’, a term denoting an enclosed settlement in otherwise wild terrain."]}]},{"name":"Matts","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Matthew  , also sometimes used as a given name in its own right."],"variants":[{"name":"Matthew","meanings":["form of the name of the Christian evangelist, author of the first gospel in the New Testament. His name is a form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i>, meaning ‘gift of God’, which is fairly common in the Old Testament, being rendered in the Authorized Version in a number of different forms: <i>Mattan(i)ah</i>, <i>Mattatha(h)</i>, <i>Mattithiah</i>, <i>Mattathias</i>, and so on. In the Authorized Version, the evangelist is regularly referred to as <i>Matthew</i>, while the apostle chosen to replace Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":76,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Matts Erlandsson Kagg was born about 1360, in Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Sweden. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Matts Erlandsson Kagg. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"abt 1360–":"umbes 1360–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1385–1472":"1385–1472","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1436":"1436","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1472":"1472","1360":"1360","about 1385":"umbes 1385","Floda, Södermanland, Sweden":"Floda, Södermanland, Rootsi","Rossvik Husby rekbaren":"Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Rootsi","Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Sweden":"Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Rootsi"},"fi":{"abt 1360–":"noin 1360–Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1385–1472":"1385–1472","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1436":"1436","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","abt 1360":"noin 1360","1472":"1472","1360":"1360","about 1385":"noin 1385","Floda, Södermanland, Sweden":"Floda, Södermanland, Ruotsi","Rossvik Husby rekbaren":"Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Ruotsi","Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Sweden":"Rossvik, Husby-Rekarne, Södermanland, Ruotsi"},"fr":{"abt 13